    ConstructorNode, DestructorNode

    public class MethodNode
extends InstanceDeclarationNode
    DeclarationNode extension that represents the declaration of a method node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location, boolean, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • getParameterListNode

        public ParameterListNode getParameterListNode()
        The the ParameterListNode that represents the parameters of the method.
        For example:
         public void methodName(int age, String name);
        In the previous statement, the data within the parenthesis are the parameters of the method. The ParameterListNode returned by this method would contain a node for each of the parameter specified, in the correct order from left to right.
        Returns:
        The ParameterListNode that represents the parameters of the method.

      • getParameterNode

        public ParameterNode getParameterNode(int parameterIndex)
        Get the ParameterNode that the given index represents. The parameters are ordered from left to right, 0 being the first.

        For example: 
         public void run(int a, int b, int c)
 {
        ...
 }
        If you were to call getParameterNode(2) on the method above, you would receive the c ParameterNode.
        Parameters:
        parameterIndex - The index parameter to get.
        Returns:
        The ParameterNode at the given index.

      • setExternal

        public void setExternal(boolean external)
        Description copied from class: VariableNode
        Set whether or not the variable is external. A variable is external if it is referenced from a language outside of Nova. For example, a variable from the C language. Furthermore, a variable is external if it begins with an externally imported C file's name.

        For example: 
         import "externalFile.h";
 
 ...
 
 public static void main(String args[])
 {
        // This is the external variable declaration.
        externalFile.externalType varName;
        
        // This is the external variable assignment.
        varName = externalFile.variableInstance;
 }
        In this example, 'externalFile' is the C header file that is imported. 'variableInstance' is the name of a variable that is contained within the imported header file.
        Overrides:
        setExternal in class VariableNode
        Parameters:
        external - Whether or not the variable will be external.
        See Also:
        VariableNode.setExternal(boolean)

      • generateCSourcePrototype

        public java.lang.String generateCSourcePrototype()
        Generate the C prototype for the method header.

        For example: 
         public void test()
 {
        ...
 }
        will output as "static void test();"

        In essence, this method is just generateCSourceSignature() with a semi-colon attached to the end.
        Returns:
        The C prototype for the method header.

        public java.lang.String generateCSourceName()

      • decodeStatement

        public static MethodNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                         java.lang.String statement,
                         Location location,
                         boolean require,
                         boolean scope)
        Decode the given statement into a MethodNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Example inputs include:
        • public Person findPerson(String name, int age)
        • private int calculateArea(int width, int height)
        • public void doNothing()
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a MethodNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        scope - Whether or not the given statement is the beginning of a scope.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a MethodNode.

      • interactWord

        public void interactWord(java.lang.String word,
                int wordNumber,
                Bounds bounds,
                int numWords,
                java.lang.String leftDelimiter,
                java.lang.String rightDelimiter,
                TreeNode.ExtraData extra)
        Description copied from class: TreeNode
        Method that is to be overridden. Whenever the iterateWords(String) method is called, this method will be called with the specific word and the number (order) the word came in the statement.
        Overrides:
        interactWord in class TreeNode
        Parameters:
        word - The word that was found.
        wordNumber - The index of the word on a word-by-word basis.
        bounds - The bounds of the word that was found.
        numWords - The number of words that were parsed.
        leftDelimiter - The text that is between the previous word and the current word.
        rightDelimiter - The text that is between the current word and the next word.
        extra - The extra data that may or may not be needed for the interactWord() methods.
        See Also:
        TreeNode.interactWord(java.lang.String, int, net.fathomsoft.nova.util.Bounds, int, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.TreeNode.ExtraData)
